&lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/domains/hohfeldian/terms/hohfeldian-waiver/>
  rdf:type schema:Article ;
  schema:url &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/domains/hohfeldian/terms/hohfeldian-waiver/> ;
  schema:name "Waiver" ;
  schema:description "A Waiver is a triple (Q, C, ω) — a right-holder Q, a Hohfeldian claim or immunity C held by Q in H*_{t*}, and a waiver act ω that drives C from H*_{t*} to ⊥_{t*}. The defining structure: waiver is unilateral relinquishment of a right by the right-holder — Q alone can waive Q's own right; the correlative obligor's consent is not required and the obligor cannot prevent it. After ω, C is extinguished: the correlative duty that had burdened the obligor is discharged. Formally: waiver is the retraction of C's section from H*_{t*} to ⊥ via the transferring nucleus Δ_{t*} applied in the dissolving direction — the right that had transferred into the doubly-settled layer is driven back to the bottom element." ;
  schema:datePublished "2026-03-20" ;
  schema:dateModified "2026-03-20" ;
  schema:about &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/domains/hohfeldian/terms/hohfeldian-waiver/> ;
  rdfs:seeAlso "HohfeldianPosition, Right, Duty, Contract, Breach, Estoppel, Novation, Revocation" ;
  schema:identifier &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/domains/hohfeldian/terms/hohfeldian-waiver/> .

